Mark A. Lathrop v. Kimberly-Clark Corporation et al. (9597)

Düpont, C. J., Spallone and O’Connell, Js.

Argued May 2 decision released May 28, 1991 Brewster Blackall, assistant attorney general, with whom, on the brief, were Richard Blumenthal, attor*838ney general, and Charles A. Over end and Cori-Lynn S. Webber, assistant attorneys general, for the appellant (defendant second injury and compensation assurance fund). Philip F. Spillane, for the appellee (plaintiff). Per Curiam.

The judgment is affirmed.
